What is Nectin-4 ADC Drugs?
Nectin-4-directed antibody-drug conjugates (ADCs) are targeted cancer therapies where a monoclonal antibody binds specifically to the cell-surface protein Nectin-4 (PVRL4), chemically linked to a cytotoxic payload via a stable or cleavable linker. Upon binding to tumor cells, the ADC is internalized, releasing the payload intracellularly to induce cancer cell death while minimizing systemic toxicity-a key advantage over traditional chemotherapy.
